(280, 0, '2020-09-03 20:14:40', '2020-09-03 20:14:40', 'The UN’s top official in Afghanistan has warned that with the formal launch of direct peace negotiations imminent, near-record violence in the country is creating an atmosphere of mistrust that risks derailing long-sought talks between the Government and the Taliban. ', 'Afghanistan: Near-record violence risks derailing imminent talks between Government and Taliban', 'The UN’s top official in Afghanistan has warned that with the formal launch of direct peace negotiations imminent, near-record violence in the country is creating an atmosphere of mistrust that risks derailing long-sought talks between the Government and the Taliban. ', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'afghanistan-near-record-violence-risks-derailing-imminent-talks-between-government-and-taliban', '', '', '2020-09-03 20:14:40', '2020-09-03 20:14:40', '', 0, 'http://localhost/HRnews.local/?post_type=wprss_feed_item&p=280', 0, 'wprss_feed_item', '', 0),
(281, 0, '2020-08-29 04:30:05', '2020-08-29 04:30:05', 'Whilst no country can claim to have beaten COVID-19, some countries have been noticeably more effective in curbing the spread of the disease. Kamal Malhotra, the UN Resident Coordinator in Viet Nam, explains why the country’s response to the pandemic has been so successful.', 'The key to Viet Nam’s successful COVID-19 response: A UN Resident Coordinator blog', 'Whilst no country can claim to have beaten COVID-19, some countries have been noticeably more effective in curbing the spread of the disease. Kamal Malhotra, the UN Resident Coordinator in Viet Nam, explains why the country’s response to the pandemic has been so successful.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-key-to-viet-nams-successful-covid-19-response-a-un-resident-coordinator-blog', '', '', '2020-08-29 04:30:05', '2020-08-29 04:30:05', '', 0, 'http://localhost/HRnews.local/?post_type=wprss_feed_item&p=281', 0, 'wprss_feed_item', '', 0),
(282, 0, '2020-08-28 07:13:50', '2020-08-28 07:13:50', 'The Government of Myanmar should embrace upcoming national elections, scheduled for November, as an opportunity to take a new and fully inclusive democratic path, and to address the root of causes of abuses suffered by ethnic minorities, the UN human rights office (OHCHR) has urged. ', 'Myanmar: Upcoming elections an opportunity to take a new inclusive democratic path', 'The Government of Myanmar should embrace upcoming national elections, scheduled for November, as an opportunity to take a new and fully inclusive democratic path, and to address the root of causes of abuses suffered by ethnic minorities, the UN human rights office (OHCHR) has urged. ', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'myanmar-upcoming-elections-an-opportunity-to-take-a-new-inclusive-democratic-path', '', '', '2020-08-28 07:13:50', '2020-08-28 07:13:50', '', 0, 'http://localhost/HRnews.local/?post_type=wprss_feed_item&p=282', 0, 'wprss_feed_item', '', 0),
(283, 0, '2020-08-26 08:04:41', '2020-08-26 08:04:41', 'UN Secretary-General António Guterres has called for greater attention to the Rohingya refugee crisis – which entered its fourth year – and for addressing the root causes of the conflict. ', 'Address root causes of the Rohingya refugee crisis, urges UN chief', 'UN Secretary-General António Guterres has called for greater attention to the Rohingya refugee crisis – which entered its fourth year – and for addressing the root causes of the conflict. ', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'address-root-causes-of-the-rohingya-refugee-crisis-urges-un-chief', '', '', '2020-08-26 08:04:41', '2020-08-26 08:04:41', '', 0, 'http://localhost/HRnews.local/?post_type=wprss_feed_item&p=283', 0, 'wprss_feed_item', '', 0),
(284, 0, '2020-08-25 11:17:05', '2020-08-25 11:17:05', 'Three years into the Rohingya refugee crisis, women, men and children – driven from their homes in Myanmar into camps across the border in Bangladesh – are more vulnerable than ever, UN agencies have reported. ', 'Three years after exodus, Rohingya refugees ‘more vulnerable than ever’', 'Three years into the Rohingya refugee crisis, women, men and children – driven from their homes in Myanmar into camps across the border in Bangladesh – are more vulnerable than ever, UN agencies have reported. ', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'three-years-after-exodus-rohingya-refugees-more-vulnerable-than-ever', '', '', '2020-08-25 11:17:05', '2020-08-25 11:17:05', '', 0, 'http://localhost/HRnews.local/?post_type=wprss_feed_item&p=284', 0, 'wprss_feed_item', '', 0),
(285, 0, '2020-08-25 04:30:05', '2020-08-25 04:30:05', 'Tourism is Hawaii’s biggest industry, with some 10 million visitors to the lslands ever year. But that has all changed since the COVID-19 pandemic, and many businesses on the archipelago have been forced to shut down for good, according to a helicopter pilot who flies pleasure trips for tourists.', 'First Person: Tourism in Hawaii grounded during pandemic', 'Tourism is Hawaii’s biggest industry, with some 10 million visitors to the lslands ever year. But that has all changed since the COVID-19 pandemic, and many businesses on the archipelago have been forced to shut down for good, according to a helicopter pilot who flies pleasure trips for tourists.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'first-person-tourism-in-hawaii-grounded-during-pandemic', '', '', '2020-08-25 04:30:05', '2020-08-25 04:30:05', '', 0, 'http://localhost/HRnews.local/?post_type=wprss_feed_item&p=285', 0, 'wprss_feed_item', '', 0),
(286, 0, '2020-08-24 04:30:05', '2020-08-24 04:30:05', 'Polio, a deadly, debilitating, yet easily curable disease, is eradicated in most countries, but is still endemic in Pakistan, partly due to a reluctance to vaccinate amongst some parts of the population. Dennis Chimenya, a health worker with the UN Children’s Fund, UNICEF, is part of a team trying to counter misconceptions, and save lives.', 'First Person: Fighting anti-vaccination rumours in Pakistan', 'Polio, a deadly, debilitating, yet easily curable disease, is eradicated in most countries, but is still endemic in Pakistan, partly due to a reluctance to vaccinate amongst some parts of the population. Dennis Chimenya, a health worker with the UN Children’s Fund, UNICEF, is part of a team trying to counter misconceptions, and save lives.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'first-person-fighting-anti-vaccination-rumours-in-pakistan', '', '', '2020-08-24 04:30:05', '2020-08-24 04:30:05', '', 0, 'http://localhost/HRnews.local/?post_type=wprss_feed_item&p=286', 0, 'wprss_feed_item', '', 0),
(287, 0, '2020-08-21 16:19:47', '2020-08-21 16:19:47', 'Three years after violence in Myanmar forced hundreds of thousands of Rohingyas to seek refuge in Bangladesh, the international community must adapt its assistance to the critical needs of those displaced and the host communities supporting them, the UN refugee agency (UNHCR) said on Friday. ', 'Rohingya crisis needs lasting solutions, renewed commitment amid COVID-19 pandemic, UN refugee agency', 'Three years after violence in Myanmar forced hundreds of thousands of Rohingyas to seek refuge in Bangladesh, the international community must adapt its assistance to the critical needs of those displaced and the host communities supporting them, the UN refugee agency (UNHCR) said on Friday. ', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'rohingya-crisis-needs-lasting-solutions-renewed-commitment-amid-covid-19-pandemic-un-refugee-agency', '', '', '2020-08-21 16:19:47', '2020-08-21 16:19:47', '', 0, 'http://localhost/HRnews.local/?post_type=wprss_feed_item&p=287', 0, 'wprss_feed_item', '', 0),
